Yoruba Nation agitator, Sunday Adeyemo, aka as Sunday Igboho, is set to storm Lagos for Yoruba Nation rally. The Yoruba Nation protesters have held rallies across southwest states, including Osun, Ogun, Ekiti, and Ondo. Igboho Igboho had in the past weeks expressed dissatisfaction over the continuous activities of killer herders in the south-west region. In the last rally held in Ekiti, Igboho declared the 2023 general elections would not hold in the region unless the Oduduwa Republic is created, calling on all stakeholders to support him and other leaders in achieving it. Igboho is expected to be in Lagos on July 3, 2021 at the Ojota park in continuation of the rally for creation of Yoruba Nation, the Nation reports. An ardent support of the activist, Ololade Alaba Shomuyiwa, popularly known as Baba Confirm, Prophet of El Adonai Cherubim and Seraphim International Bible Ministries, disclosed that Igboho and other supporters would be in Lagos, urging Yoruba to support the movement.